Guangxi University Students' Heritage and Entrepreneurship have the longest to reach 5 years-Xinhua News Agency, Xinhua News Agency, Nanning, May 19th (Reporter Zhang Ying) Reporter recently learned from the Education Department of the Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region that universities in Guangxi will implement an elastic scientific system in the future to relax the school students of college students.	 The time of school students' suspension and entrepreneurship can be extended for 2 to 5 years on the basis of the original academic system.	 In order to promote the improvement of college students' entrepreneurship and innovation capabilities, Guangxi Education, Human Resources and other departments work together to build an entrepreneurial platform, build more college students' off -school practical teaching bases, university science and technology parks, college student entrepreneurial parks, entrepreneurial incubation bases, etc., and provide external guarantees for college students' entrepreneurship.	 According to the requirements, by 2020, the area of innovation and entrepreneurship practice base in various universities will reach more than 3,000 square meters, and higher vocational schools will reach more than 2,000 square meters.	 The government encourages universities to set up innovative and entrepreneurial credits to give priority to supporting students who have performed well in innovation and entrepreneurship. College teachers go to industry enterprises to exercise at least two months every two years, thereby improving the awareness and ability of teachers' innovation and entrepreneurial education.	 The Education Department of the Autonomous Region requires universities in Guangxi to implement college students' innovation and entrepreneurship training programs, and strive to enable each college student to participate in an innovative and entrepreneurial training plan during school.	 Universities must actively organize students to participate in various levels of innovation and entrepreneurship competitions at all levels and give funding support.
